		<div id="comment_body_64430500"><p>They don't need to hire such engineers. There's no huge problem with having Boeing's own engineers certify stuff that Boeing builds. You just have to hold them liable and punish them appropriately when stuff happens.</p><p>Happens for other fields: <span class="substr"> </span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Regulation_and_licensure_in_engineering#Legislative_intent" title="wikipedia.org" rel="nofollow">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/...</a> [wikipedia.org] </p><p>So if there's a high chance you'd go to prison etc if shit happens, even if Boeing is your employer there'd be a limit to how much you'd bend over for Boeing's management, and you'd definitely make backups of evidence to cover your butt.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64430500">

</div>
